JOHANNESBURG - Moody's said on Tuesday that it would not issue a sovereign credit rating decision on South Africa this Friday, as previously planned, but will do so after a review that could take 30 to 90 days.Moody's announced on Monday that it had placed South Africa on a review for a downgrade after a cabinet reshuffle that saw a respected former finance minister dismissed from his post.READ: Moody's considers South Africa's investment ratingMoody's currently has South Africa's sovereign rating at two notches above non-investment grade at Baa2. Reuters